# 13. Interview Questions

### What are Guardrails?

Safety mechanisms that ensure AI systems operate within predefined rules and policies.

---

### Why are Guardrails important?

They improve safety, reliability, compliance, and security.

---

### Name four types of Guardrails.

- Input Guardrails
- Output Guardrails
- Tool Guardrails
- Human Approval

---

### Are prompts and guardrails the same thing?

No.

Prompts guide model behavior.

Guardrails enforce system-level safety and validation.

---

### What is the Principle of Least Privilege?

Only granting an AI system the minimum permissions required to complete its task.

